CAPE TOWN - Public Accounts Committee chairperson Themba Godi maintains Parliament does not answer to Cabinet.He was responding to President Jacob Zuma s appeal for government officials not to speak or comment publicly on the Sassa issue."Talking to the country and answering questions is not helping. In fact, it helps to fertilise the situation where people are speculating, Zuma had said.READ: 'No crisis' says President Zuma of Sassa debacle"We do not take our cue from Cabinet and we will continue to probe and ask questions in relation to this matter," he said."I would imagine that in a situation of such great anxiety, certainly, the last thing is to deny people information," Godi added. eNCA